CIPC Business Press Ltd G456785a   C  1p Notes on Appliances:

ECookersGDon't put a cooker on opposite  side of kitchen from sink,behind a door or near a window if it is gas.
 Do have a putting down surface on at
 least one side of the hob and oven

CRefrigerator/freezerGDoors usually
 hinged on right. Leave 80mm gap for
 motor ventilation

FWashing machine/dishwasherGPlace near
 sink. Leave 100mm gap at back for hoses and 50mm gap each side for pulling out 
 Maximum walking distance between fridge sink and cooker should form triangle of 6 metres
